<div class="sh"><h2>Key metrics explained</h2></div>
<div class="g2">
<div class="cc">
<div class="ct">WIS - Withdrawal Impact Score</div>
<div class="prose">
<p>Percentage of total traces that are withdrawals. Withdrawals are harder to obtain than deposits and more valuable to clients because they reveal where funds flow out of an exchange.</p>
<p><strong>Formula:</strong> Withdrawals / Total Traces x 100</p>
<p><strong>Target:</strong> 40-50%</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cc">
<div class="ct">TVS - Trace Value Score</div>
<div class="prose">
<p>Quality-weighted score that rewards higher-value trace types (withdrawals over deposits) and higher-value discovery types (retracing already-known entities over first-time discovery).</p>
<p><strong>Formula:</strong> TVS = (C1 + C2) / 2 / total traces</p>
<p><strong>C1 (trace type):</strong> Deposit = 2pts, Withdrawal = 3pts, Wdr PSP = 1pt</p>
<p><strong>C2 (discovery):</strong> Dep retrace = 1pt, First-time = 2pts, Wdr retrace = 3pts</p>
<p><strong>Target:</strong> 3.0 (2025 baseline: 2.1)</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
